## **Incumbent Competitors — Detailed Profiles**

**EnergyCAP — Primary Incumbent**

- Founded: 1980 (State College, PA). CEO: Shawn Lankton. PE-backed by Resurgens Technology Partners (2021). Revenue: ~$21.5M (2025, Orbis/Cortera). Employees: 90.

- Target: Higher education (19% of users), government (19%), large commercial — organizations with 100–1,000+ meters

- Market position: Named Market Leader in FeaturedCustomers Summer 2024; Info-Tech Champion 2025. 10,000+ customers. '40+ years helping clients succeed.'

- Pricing: Express $4,000/year (~$40/meter, 100 meters); Enterprise $13,000/year (~$52/meter, 250 meters); implementation fees $5,000–$100,000+

- Strengths: Deep utility bill accounting; meter hierarchy management; campus chargeback; ENERGY STAR integration; carbon accounting add-ons; 40-year installed base

Verified weaknesses from 132 G2/Capterra user reviews (4.7/5 overall — high satisfaction but consistent UX frustrations):

- 'Hundreds of reports whose names or descriptions don't always help. And the more reports that are added, the more the waters are muddied'

- 'The chargebacks and splits are hard to understand. I tried to use the help, but it is lacking details'

- 'Outdated, un-intuitive, glorified spreadsheet' — actual review title on Capterra

- 'Recommendations for upgrades/improvements to reports tend to come back as a very simple: We can't do that'

- Non-January fiscal year creates confusion: 'Actually misleading for reporting'

- Long-tenured users remain undertrained: 'I have been using EnergyCAP for 8 years and I know there are plenty of ways to use the system but I just don't know how'

- Implementation is time-intensive; spotty data with gaps; limited mobile experience

**Arcadia — Primary AI-Native Competitor (HIGH THREAT)**

- Funding: $649M total raised; $1.5B valuation (unicorn). ~$270M estimated ARR. 300+ enterprise customers including Ford.

- Strategic pivot: January 2025 launch of Arcadia Enterprise Solutions — directly targeting utility bill management, energy procurement advisory, and supply management. This is the same use case as Clear Current.

- Data moat: Acquired Urjanet 2022 — now covers 95%+ of U.S. utility accounts. 99% energy cost accuracy claim. Automated 500,000+ meter-tariff assignments.

- Key gap: Built as B2B data infrastructure, not purpose-built for energy manager UX. Enterprise direct-sales motion still maturing post-pivot. No campus chargeback focus. No higher ed vertical depth.

**Schneider Electric Resource Advisor+ — Incumbent Accelerating**

- January 2026 launch of Resource Advisor+ with AI agent 'Sera' — orchestrates sub-agents across carbon tracking, ESG reporting, and energy procurement

- Oriented toward ESG compliance for large multinationals; not billing accuracy focused. Requires Schneider hardware ecosystem for full value. IDC and Verdantix Leader.

**Siemens Building X / Navigator**

- Hardware-first company — subscription by meter, minimum 10 meters. ML-based anomaly detection but no tariff intelligence or billing audit capability.

- User sentiment: Reddit/r/BuildingAutomation: 'I have literally heard not a single person who likes Desigo' — referring to Siemens' building management platform.

**Johnson Controls OpenBlue**

- ~$23B revenue; record $12B services backlog in FY2024. Strong in healthcare and education but hardware/ESPC contract model, not SaaS.

- Energy layer exists but no utility bill auditing capability.

**AI-Native Emerging Players**

- Verse Inc. — AI platform 'Aria' for energy procurement, PPA management, and risk modeling. 'Built by energy buyers for energy buyers.' Upstream from billing audit. Potential partner rather than direct competitor.

- iem — Raised $75M Series B in February 2026 to scale AI-native energy transaction infrastructure. Focused on energy markets automation.

- Nectar (YC-backed) — 'The modern AI energy management platform.' Targets facility managers and ESG teams. SaaS, mid-market accessible. No campus focus.

- Gridium — Energy-management-as-a-service for commercial real estate. $470–833/month. Hardware-free subscription. AI diagnostics.

## **Clear Current****'****s Competitive Gap — The Positioning Thesis**

| **OPPORTUNITY** | No single vendor currently combines: (1) Billing audit depth — EnergyCAP's core, but aging UX. (2) Tariff optimization at scale — Arcadia strong, but no campus focus. (3) PPA/contract management — Verse strong, but no billing audit. (4) Campus chargeback intelligence — EnergyCAP only, with documented UX failures. (5) AI-native interface — none of the incumbents. Clear Current is the only platform positioned to do all five. |
