## **U.S. Smart Meter Adoption**

| **Metric** | **Figure** | **Source** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Total U.S. smart meters installed (2024) | 136.9 million (~82% of electric meters) | EIA / IOT Analytics |
| Projected penetration by 2030 | ~91% of all U.S. electric meters | IOT Analytics |
| Residential share of AMI installations | ~88% of all U.S. AMI | EIA CBECS / AMR |
| Commercial sub-metering penetration (2018) | ~10% of commercial buildings | EIA CBECS 2018 |
| Commercial smart meter market size (2023) | $5.2B | GM Insights |
| Commercial AMI CAGR through 2031 | 12.92% | AMR Research |
| AMI market total (2024) | $4.5B, projected $9.0B | Yahoo Finance / AMR |
| AMI 2.0 data frequency | 96+ readings/day per meter at leading utilities | Utility Analytics Institute |

| **CRITICAL NUANCE** | The 82% smart meter headline is heavily skewed by residential installations. Commercial sub-metering was only ~10% as of 2018 (EIA CBECS). The commercial/industrial AMI segment is growing fastest (12.92% CAGR) but starts from a low base. This means most commercial customers still receive monthly billing reads — exactly the limitation that makes AI-powered billing audit software valuable today, and interval data analytics the near-term product evolution. |
| --- | --- |

## **What Interval Data Enables for Commercial Customers**

| **Capability** | **Monthly-Only Billing Data** | **With 5/15-Minute Interval Data** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Demand charge analysis | See total monthly peak demand | Identify which 15-min window set the peak; model demand reduction scenarios |
| Time-of-use optimization | Limited to bill totals | Map consumption to on-peak vs. off-peak; model rate switching |
| Fault detection | Discover anomalies 30+ days late | Detect equipment malfunction or occupancy violations in near-real time |
| Load shaping | Reactive only | Proactive — shift loads before peak window to avoid demand charge ratchets |
| Benchmarking | Building-vs-building comparisons | Hour-by-hour benchmarking with weather normalization |
| PPA/contract optimization | Limited | Model actual consumption profiles against alternative rate structures |

