| **10** | **Source Credibility Audit ****&**** Recommended Substitutions** |
| --- | --- |

This section documents the outcome of an independent claim verification session (Research Session 3). Each statistic was evaluated for source credibility, conflict of interest, and whether an independent corroborating source was available.

| **Claim** | **Original Source** | **Credibility** | **Conflict of Interest?** | **Action** |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| '80% of businesses overpay on utilities' | nationalutilitiesrefund.com | LOW | Severe — vendor profits from finding errors | DO NOT USE — substitute with FERC/PUC enforcement examples |
| '$241B commercial energy spend 2024' | Derived from EIA 2018 + price adjustment | MEDIUM | None — EIA is government | USE WITH QUALIFICATION — label as price-adjusted estimate |
| '98% rate energy efficiency as important; 9% use software' | GridPoint 2023 vendor survey | LOW | Significant — GridPoint sells EMS | REPLACE — use EIA 4% BEMS; EPA 25% Portfolio Manager |
| '5–15% of bills contain errors' | 360 Energy, National Utility Refund, Conservice | LOW precision / MEDIUM directional | All three profit from finding errors | USE DIRECTIONALLY — attribute as industry auditor estimate; support with FERC/PUC evidence |
| 'Universities spend $6B on energy' | Misattributed / outdated figure | INCORRECT | None — just wrong | CORRECT: K-12 = $8B+ (EPA); Higher Ed = $8–11B (derived) |
| 'Only 9% of companies use energy management software' | GridPoint 2023 vendor survey | LOW | Same conflict as above | REPLACE — use EIA 4% BEMS; EPA 25% Portfolio Manager |

