## **Market Entry Recommendations — Research-Backed**

The following recommendations are drawn directly from the convergence of primary interview findings and secondary research:

| **Recommendation** | **Research Basis** | **Urgency** |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Lead with billing audit as the entry value prop — create immediate, quantifiable ROI before software commitment | Regulatory evidence (FERC $108M, RI PUC 83%); Marc Spieler's proof requirement; Phil Combs' client reactive pattern | Immediate |
| Target higher education as initial beachhead vertical | EnergyCAP weakness concentration in this segment; campus chargeback gap; Andee Chamberlain / Andi Ault primary research; $8–11B spend | Immediate |
| Build campus chargeback as a differentiated, well-designed platform capability (not a bolt-on) | No AI-native competitor offers this; EnergyCAP's most important feature with its worst UX; required for higher ed moat | Near-term (6–12 months) |
| Develop the Arcadia competitive response now | Arcadia's January 2025 enterprise pivot + $649M funding makes it the clearest direct threat; window is narrowing | Immediate |
| Build a documented error recovery case study from existing pilots | Marc Spieler: 'The concept's great. The question is, how often are these bills wrong?' — investors will ask this; no published proof point exists | Immediate — pre-fundraise priority |
| Position ahead of ESG reporting deadlines (CSRD Wave 2, California SB 253) | Andi Ault: budget submitted before knowing final rates; Verdantix: 85% of real estate executives increasing sustainability spend | 18-month window |
| Pursue ERP/billing software licensing strategy as parallel distribution channel | Marc Spieler: 'embed it into somebody else's billing thing... you just have to sell to QuickBooks and QuickBooks sells to everybody else' | Medium-term |
| Apply to NVIDIA Inception program if NVIDIA GPU infrastructure is in the stack | Marc Spieler: free, no equity, VC introductions, enterprise matchmaking — 'a no-brainer' | Near-term (quick win) |

*This document was compiled by the CDL MBA Consulting Team (Clayton Hester, Jason Wisnieski, Adam Case, Victor Pan) in support of the Clear Current Technologies CDL engagement (March–April 2026). Research was conducted using TAMU Library databases, Perplexity Deep Research, EIA government data, and direct sourcing. All statistics have been credibility-rated. Statistics marked HIGH-credibility are government or independent sources; MEDIUM-credibility statistics are from reputable trade sources; LOW-credibility statistics have been flagged for replacement. Do not use LOW-credibility statistics in investor or customer-facing materials without substitution.*